headline.main: YEARBOOK DEPICTS SOVIET SPACESHIP; Editor of Jane's '65 Edition Cites Kremlin Cooperation

results.snippet: LONDON, Nov. 28 (AP) -- Signs of a relaxation in Soviet military secrecy appeared today in the new edition of the yearbook Jane's All the World's Aircraft. It carries a description of how Soviet astronauts are ejected from their space capsules at...
results.lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 28 (AP) -- Signs of a relaxation in Soviet military secrecy appeared today in the new edition of the yearbook Jane's All the World's Aircraft. It carries a description of how Soviet astronauts are ejected from their space capsules at 23,000 fee after reentry.
